SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 550
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend R. Larry Smith of Knox
County for decades of devoted service to the
State of Tennessee.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is R. Larry Smith of Knox County, a
consummate professional whose service to his community and this State have improved the
well-being of countless individuals and organizations; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Smith earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Wildlife and Fisheries
Science from the University of Tennessee, Knoxville (UT) and went on to work with the
Tennessee Valley Authority Fisheries and Wildlife Management Division and then the
Tennessee Wildlife Resources Agency (TWRA); and
WHEREAS, a TWRA Foundation Member, R. Larry Smith certified more than 500
graduates as a hunter safety instructor during his tenure with the TWRA, and he served as the
commissioner of the Tennessee Department of Environment and Conservation from 2001 to
2004; and
WHEREAS, in 1980, he founded R. Larry Smith & Associates Insurance Agency, thus
embarking upon a remarkable career as an insurance agency director; he would ascend to
serve as president of the Knoxville Association of Insurance and Financial Advisors and
Tennessee State president of the National Association of Insurance and Financial Advisors; and
WHEREAS, his career in insurance garnered LUTCF designation, the National Quality
Award (over four decades), the National Sales Achievement Award (over three decades), the
SJR0550
009796
- 1 -

Leadership in Life Institute Award, and the National Association of Insurance and Financial
Advisors Insurance Professional of the Year Award for the State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, R. Larry Smith was commissioner of the Metropolitan Planning Commission
of Knox County in 1997-2005 and a Knox County Commissioner in 2006-2014, serving as vice
chair in 2012 and 2013; long an engaged supporter of the Republican Party, he was chairman
of the Knox County GOP in 1992-1994; and
WHEREAS, a venerated leader throughout his community, Mr. Smith lent his time and
talents as a member of various organizations, serving on the boards of the American Cancer
Society, the American Red Cross, Tennova Hospital, Knoxville Volunteer Rescue Squad, the
YMCA, Keep Knoxville Beautiful, James White Fort, the Helen Ross McNabb Center, the Boys
& Girls Club of Knoxville, and CareCuts, Inc., a nonprofit serving the homeless population in
Knoxville; and
WHEREAS, he has further served as a member of the Truist Bank Advisory Board, TDS
Telecom Advisory Board, Knox County Community Health Improvement Council, Rural Metro
Fire Advisory Board, UT Knoxville's Alumni Board and Tip-Off Club, Knoxville Sertoma Center's
Business Advisory Committee, Better Roads in North Knoxville (BRINK), and Better Business
Bureau; and
WHEREAS, an Eagle Scout himself, R. Larry Smith has been actively involved with the
Boy Scouts of America for nearly sixty years, serving in various leadership roles, including as an
assistant Scoutmaster and member of the Smoky Mountain Council Board, and receiving
several honors, including the Silver Beaver Award and the James A. West Fellowship Award;
and
WHEREAS, his other duly awarded honors include being named Man of the Year by the
Halls Business and Professional Association, receiving the Service to Mankind Award from the
- 2 - 009796

Sertoma Club and the East Tennessee Historical Society Award of Distinction, and earning an
Honorary Letterman from the University of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, R. Larry Smith has been a member of Fountain City United Methodist
Church for more than three decades, during which time he has taught Sunday School and
served on various councils and committees; and
WHEREAS, throughout his many worthy endeavors, Mr. Smith has enjoyed the love and
support of his wife, Sharon, and their three children, and four grandchildren; and
WHEREAS, R. Larry Smith epitomizes the spirit and commitment that are characteristic
of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Mr. Smith for his many
years of dedication to the State of Tennessee and its citizens; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend R. Larry Smith for his
distinguished career in the insurance industry and his many years of public service and
leadership, extending our best wishes for every continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
